# ecommerce.merconfig
# Vocabulary, configuration, and tools for the order processing system.

=== vocabulary ===

# People

A person is a kind of thing.
A person has a name, an email, and a phone number.

A customer is a kind of person.
A customer has a status, which is one of (active, suspended, closed).
A customer has a credit limit, which is Money.
A customer has a tier, which is one of (standard, premium, enterprise).
A customer has a signup date, which is a Date.

An account manager is a kind of person.

# Email parts (semantic wrappers around String)

An email address is a kind of String.
A subject line is a kind of String.
A message body is a kind of String.

# Orders and items

An order is a kind of thing.
An order has a status, which is one of (draft, submitted, under review, approved, on hold, fulfilled, cancelled, rejected).
An order has a total amount, which is Money.
An order has a placement date, which is a Date.

A line item is a kind of thing.
A line item has a quantity, which is a Number.
A line item has a unit price, which is Money.

# Invoices

An invoice is a kind of thing.
An invoice has a status, which is one of (paid, pending, overdue, disputed).
An invoice has an amount, which is Money.
An invoice has a due date, which is a Date.

# Tool result kinds

A validation result is a kind of thing.
A validation result has a verdict, which is one of (valid, invalid).
A validation result has issues, which is a List.

A payment result is a kind of thing.
A payment result has a status, which is one of (succeeded, failed).
A payment result has an error message, which is a String.

An approval is a kind of thing.
An approval has a verdict, which is one of (approved, denied, deferred).
An approval has a note, which is a String.

# System components

A mailer server is a kind of system.
A mailer server has a host, a port, and an auth type.

A payment processor is a kind of service.
A payment processor has an api endpoint and an api key.

# Relations

places relates one customer to many orders.
The inverse of placing is being placed by.

contains relates one order to many line items.

is sent to relates one invoice to one customer.

manages relates one account manager to many customers.
The inverse of managing is being managed by.

# Phrase definitions

To validate an order:
  bind result = invoke validate order with id = the order's id.
  if the result's verdict is invalid,
    reject the order with reason "validation_failed".

To check the credit of a customer for an amount:
  bind available = invoke get available credit with customer = the customer's id.
  if available is less than the amount,
    reject the order with reason "insufficient_credit".

To put an order on hold with a reason:
  invoke update order with id = the order's id, status = "on hold".
  emit order.held with order = the order, reason = the reason.

To approve an order:
  invoke update order with id = the order's id, status = "approved".
  emit order.approved with order = the order.

To reject an order with a reason:
  invoke update order with id = the order's id, status = "rejected".
  emit order.rejected with order = the order, reason = the reason.

To send an email via a mailer server,
              to an email address,
              with a subject line,
              and a message body:
  invoke send email with
    via = the mailer server,
    to = the email address,
    subject = the subject line,
    body = the message body.

To notify a person that their order was approved:
  send an email via the primary mailer,
    to the person's email,
    with subject line "Your order is approved",
    and message body "Your order has been approved and is being prepared for fulfillment.".

To notify a person that their order is on hold because of a reason:
  send an email via the primary mailer,
    to the person's email,
    with subject line "Your order is on hold",
    and message body the reason.

To notify a person that their order was rejected because of a reason:
  send an email via the primary mailer,
    to the person's email,
    with subject line "We could not process your order",
    and message body the reason.

To screen an order for fraud for a customer:
  if the customer's signup date is within the new customer threshold,
    bind risk = invoke run fraud check with order = the order's id.
    if risk is more than the fraud risk threshold,
      put the order on hold with reason "fraud_review_required".
      notify the customer that their order is on hold because of "We are reviewing your order for security purposes. This typically takes 1 to 2 business days.".
      complete with reason "fraud_review_required".

To obtain account manager approval for an order for a customer:
  if the order's total amount is more than the high value threshold,
    bind approval = invoke request approval with
      approver = the customer's account manager's id,
      order = the order's id.
    if the approval's verdict is denied,
      reject the order with reason "approval_denied".
      notify the customer that their order was rejected because of the approval's note.
      complete with reason "approval_denied".

To finalize payment for an order placed by a customer:
  bind payment = invoke charge payment with
    via = the stripe,
    customer = the customer's id,
    amount = the order's total amount,
    order_id = the order's id.
  if the payment's status is succeeded,
    approve the order.
    notify the customer that their order was approved.
    complete.
  put the order on hold with reason "payment_failed".
  bind retry count = invoke get retry count with order = the order's id.
  if retry count is less than the maximum retry count,
    wait 1 hour.
    process the order placed by the customer.
    complete.
  reject the order with reason "max_retries_exceeded".
  notify the customer that their order was rejected because of "We could not process your payment after several attempts. Please contact support.".
  complete with reason "max_retries_exceeded".

To record analytics for an order placed by a customer:
  in lenient mode.
  emit analytics.order_processed with
    order_id = the order's id,
    customer_id = the customer's id,
    amount = the order's total amount,
    timestamp = now.

=== constants ===

The default currency is "USD".
The high value threshold is $5000.
The maximum retry count is 3.
The new customer threshold is 30 days.
The fraud risk threshold is 0.5.

=== instances ===

There is a mailer server called primary mailer:
  host = $SMTP_HOST
  port = 587
  auth type = "tls"

There is a payment processor called stripe:
  api endpoint = "https://api.stripe.com/v1"
  api key = $STRIPE_API_KEY

=== tools ===

Get Customer
============
-- Retrieve a customer by ID. Returns full customer record
-- including status, credit limit, tier, and account manager.
~ getCustomer(id: String) : Customer

Validate Order
==============
-- Run business validation rules against an order. Returns
-- a validation result with a verdict and any issues found.
~ validateOrder(id: String) : ValidationResult

Get Available Credit
====================
-- Compute available credit for a customer based on credit
-- limit minus outstanding orders and overdue invoices.
~ getAvailableCredit(customer: String) : Money

Get Overdue Invoices
====================
-- Return invoices for a customer that are past their due date.
~ getOverdueInvoices(customer: String) : List

Update Order
============
-- Update an order's status. Allowed transitions are governed
-- by the order lifecycle rules.
~ updateOrder(id: String, status: String) : Order

Send Email
==========
-- Send an email through a configured mailer server.
~ sendEmail(via: MailerServer, to: String, subject: String, body: String) : Boolean

Charge Payment
==============
-- Charge a customer's payment method through the configured
-- payment processor. Idempotent on order ID.
~ chargePayment(via: PaymentProcessor, customer: String, amount: Money, order_id: String) : PaymentResult

Run Fraud Check
===============
-- Score an order for fraud risk. Returns a number between
-- 0.0 (safe) and 1.0 (high risk).
~ runFraudCheck(order: String) : Number

Request Approval
================
-- Submit an order for human approval by an account manager.
-- Blocks until a verdict is recorded or the request times out.
~ requestApproval(approver: String, order: String) : Approval

Get Retry Count
===============
-- Return the number of times this order has been retried for payment.
~ getRetryCount(order: String) : Number
